<h3>Quake 4 game and engine:</h3>
<p>Quake 4 introduces new editors, cvars, events, file formats, directories, and the following functionality:</p>
<ul>
<li>Lipsync support</li>
<li>Guides for easier material creation</li>
<li>Improved ambient lighting</li>
<li>Squad based AI</li>
<li>Portal Skies</li>
<li><span class="plainlinks"><a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20120919085849/http://www.mfadegree.net/"><span style="font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none!important; background: none!important; text-decoration: none"><font color="black">MFA Degree</font></span></a> </span></li>
<li>CG/HLSL Shaders</li>
<li>Playback editor/entities</li>
<li>Gravity related entities</li>
<li>FX files/editor (improved particles)</li>
<li>Improved Level Editor</li>
<li>Bugfixes in GUI editor</li>
<li>Improved Networking</li>
<li>New script events</li>
<li>Tools moved into separate .dll</li>
</ul>
<p>Much of the AI and weapon functionality moved into compiled code.</p>
<p>Quake 4 was created by <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20120919085849/http://www.ravensoft.com/">Raven Software</a> and published by <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20120919085849/http://www.activision.com/">Activision</a>. Release date for the PC version was October 18, 2005.</p>
<h3>System Requirements:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Operating System: Windows 2000/XP, Mac OSX, Linux</li>
<li>CPU: Pentium 4 2.0 or Athlon XP 2000+</li>
<li>Memory: 512MB</li>
<li>Storage: 2.8GB</li>
<li>Sound: 100% DirectX 9.0c Compliant / 16-bit</li>
<li>Video: 100% DirectX 9.0c Compliant / 64MB RAM</li>
</ul>
